                            {
                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "U01QUBNJSEQ"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " Thanks! I will look into it some more. aside: Actors are not like PBP diagrams, but, maybe bigraphs are. The issue is: when implementing fan-out, where is the routing information stored? In Actors, you have to hard-wire knowledge of the destinations into the sender's code, whereas with PBP the routing information is notationally lifted into the parents' code. Bigraphs seem to get this more right. Technically this appears to be just a small issue, but it results in a major DX issue. Hard-wiring prevents LEGO-like plugability."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
